CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 19, 1954, pg. 9 reads: "Homemakers See Latest in Foods, Appliances...4. Radio Station WHOD displayed the products of several of their advertisers in their booth. Mary Dee (shown here) and Mal Goode, did a nightly broadcast from the booth...Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: WHOD disc jockey Mary Dee holding can of Breakfast Cheer coffee in trade show booth for radio station WHOD with ads including PET milk and Philip Morris, in the Hunt Armory for the 1954 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair,  another version
